lead_paragraph: On Tuesday next comes off in Pennsylvania the triennial election for Governor. The canvass has, for many reasons, been one of extreme activity and closeness. Every energy has been stimulated to its utmost. The immense personal popularity of WILLIAM F. JOHNSTON, the fortunate character of his administration, have induced the most extraordinary endeavors on the part of his friends to draw out a fill vote, which must certainly reelect their candidate.
